article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 85, Philander Smith 58
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Montrell Thornton scored 13 points and Solomon Bozeman added 12 to lead Arkansas-Little Rock to an 85-58 victory over Philander Smith on Tuesday night. Thornton was 6 of 6 from the field and one missed free throw away from a perfect shooting night for the Trojans (6-3), who have won three of four. Tim Stewart scored 10 points to lead the Panthers (0-13), an NAIA team whose campus is about 5 miles away from the Trojans'. Arkansas-Little Rock led 42-25 at halftime, shot 58.5 percent and outrebounded Philander Smith 47-31. This was the first meeting between the neighboring schools since the 1969-70 season. The Panthers still lead the all-time series, 4-3.
